This project analyzes health and lifestyle data from 44 global cities using base R functions. It was completed as part of Lab 1 for MAS342 data analysis course.

Summary
- Explored relationships between variables like gym cost, water price, happiness, and life expectancy
- Conducted descriptive statistics, scatterplots, histograms, and correlation analysis
- Interpreted trends to identify which factors most influence life satisfaction

Key Insights
- Cities with higher water costs tended to have higher happiness scores
- Gym cost was not a strong predictor of life expectancy or happiness
- Happiness was moderately correlated with life expectancy

Files
- `Lab1.Rmd`: Full annotated RMarkdown script
- `Lab1.pdf`: Knitted output with code and results
